_[toxcore/Messenger.c, line 151 at r1](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/269#-KWUzemzmtYmQ1ydY_uN:-KWUzemzmtYmQ1ydY_uO:b-vn440h) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/c-toxcore/blob/c0a29e9dc853d16d418f532b8f305c4385d0aedc/toxcore/Messenger.c#L151)):_

> ``` C
>     uint16_t checksum = address_checksum(address, FRIEND_ADDRESS_SIZE - sizeof(checksum));
>     memcpy(address + crypto_box_PUBLICKEYBYTES + sizeof(nospam), &checksum, sizeof(checksum));
> }
> ```

Here you have change the endianess of nospam returned by the `tox_self_get_address()` function, but the public API has more function that deal with nospam, like `tox_self_get_nospam()` and `tox_self_set_nospam()`. It would be weird if `tox_self_get_address()` suddenly starts returning nospam in one endianess and `tox_self_get_nospam()` in another.

